[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer security sanitizer detected a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m issue of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmedium severity when the M3U8ParserFuzzer harness triggered an outbound network [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnection. The fuzzer input caused the code to attempt a TCP connection to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m,” which was flagged by the SSRF protection logic.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The Jazzer framework raised a [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium exception indicating an [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSSRF condition. The sanitizer prevented a socket connection to an external host [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mderived from untrusted data.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exception originates in [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheckSsrfSocket, indicating a security check in the fuzzer runtime.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A java.net.Socket.connect call is intercepted, followed by HTTP client [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitialization in java.net and sun.net.www.http.HttpClient.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The data flow continues into HttpURLConnection.connect and getInputStream, then[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto Apache Tika’s TikaInputStream.get methods.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Control reaches org.apache.tika.parser.m3.M3U8Parser.handleLink and parse, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshowing that the parser attempts to fetch or probe external URIs found in M3U8 [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplaylist content.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcom.example.M3U8ParserFuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes parseOne and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzerTestOneInput, which drive the parsing of provided inputs.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate for a holistic view  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • org.apache.tika.parser.m3.M3U8Parser.handleLink [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m170[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – logic that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolves or fetches links in playlist entries  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • org.apache.tika.parser.m3.M3U8Parser._parse and parse methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m92[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – orchestration of parsing and link handling  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • TikaInputStream.get [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m570[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m606[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – opening streams to external resources  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Use of HttpURLConnection and underlying HttpClient in the codebase  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserFuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how inputs reach the parser[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand trigger network operations[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mex.parseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtis, new [0m[1;35mBodyContentHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mEmbeddedContentHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxhtml[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, m,[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:                        true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The SSRF originates in M3U8Parser.handleLink: any playlist line beginning with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“http” is assumed safe and passed directly to new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnextLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mTikaInputStream.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggering an unguarded HTTP connection.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no whitelist/blacklist or configuration flag to disable or validate [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fetches in the M3U8 parser, so untrusted inputs can force network [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Design Goals[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prevent unvalidated [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m network calls by default, eliminating SSRF risk.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Preserve existing logic that records playlist links in metadata [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;35mmetadata.add[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPLAY_LIST_LINK, nextLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allow downstream consumers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapplications embedding Tika[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to opt in to external[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresource fetching, if truly desired, via an explicit configuration flag in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParseContext.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Avoid any changes to harness, fuzzing, or test code. Existing tests should [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to pass under the new default [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno external fetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. High-Level Fix Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Introduce a new parser-specific configuration class, e.g. `M3U8ParserConfig`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a boolean flag `allowExternalLinks` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault: false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • This class is used as a ParseContext key:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public class M3U8ParserConfig [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            private final boolean allowExternalLinks;  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            public [0m[1;35mM3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis.allowExternalLinks = allowExternalLinks; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            public boolean [0m[1;35misAllowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return allowExternalLinks; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In the public `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream stream, ContentHandler handler, Metadata [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata, ParseContext context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method of `M3U8Parser`, retrieve the config:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • `M3U8ParserConfig cfg = [0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • `boolean permitFetch = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcfg != null && [0m[1;35mcfg.isAllowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Modify `[0m[1;35mhandleLink[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around lines [0m[1;36m164[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m167[0m[39m to conditionally perform the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal fetch only if `permitFetch` is true:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m after [0m[1;35mmetadata.add[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPLAY_LIST_LINK, nextLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnextLine.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m NEW: Check config flag before network fetch[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!permitFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Skip external fetch, preventing SSRF[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Preserve the existing `EmbeddedDocumentExtractor` logic; only surround it [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith this new guard. No other changes to parsing or metadata accumulation are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeded.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Document in Javadoc on `M3U8Parser` that external link fetching is disabled [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby default and explain how to opt into it:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * By default, external [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m URIs are recorded in metadata but not [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetched.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * To enable embedded fetching of external segments, supply a[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link M3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m with [0m[33mallowExternalLinks[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m in the ParseContext:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *   [0m[1;35mcontext.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserConfig.class, new [0m[1;35mM3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. Add a unit test for the new behavior:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Provide a small playlist with an “[0m[4;94mhttp://example.com/segment.ts[0m[39m” link.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Assert that with default context, no network fetch occurs [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. by mocking [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaInputStream.get or by verifying no exception[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Assert that with `[0m[33mallowExternalLinks[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`, the fetch logic is invoked [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcan[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe a dummy stubbed URL or a local HTTP test server[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Disabling external fetch by default completely eliminates the SSRF attack [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msurface while preserving metadata extraction.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introducing a ParseContext flag conforms with Tika’s pluggable, opt-in design [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor parser-specific behavior.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests and harness code remain unchanged; users who depend on external fetch [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan explicitly opt in, so existing codebases are unaffected unless they explicitly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menable the new config.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Avoids broad exception catching: network calls are never invoked under [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted inputs unless explicitly allowed.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This pattern mirrors other Tika parsers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., XML parser disables DTD [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetching by default with a flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and maintains consistency in security posture.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream users expecting automatic external segment fetching will see [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing embedded content. [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Mitigation: clearly document new default behavior; provide examples to enable [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe flag.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If finer-grained host validation is required in the future, a more advanced [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mURL whitelist/blacklist can be layered atop this config without altering the public[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Required Code Ranges to Patch[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-audiovideo-module/src/main[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m/java/org/apache/tika/parser/m3/M3U8Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:70[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-audiovideo-module/src/main[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m/java/org/apache/tika/parser/m3/M3U8Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:150[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m174[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-audiovideo-module/src/main[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m/java/org/apache/tika/parser/m3/M3U8ParserConfig.jav[0m[1;92ma:1[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m20[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn SSRF vulnerability was identified when the M3U8Parser fetched external links [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbased on untrusted data, triggering a Jazzer FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium exception [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor attempted network access. A patch was proposed that adds a nested [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`M3U8ParserConfig` class [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith Tika `@Field`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`@Param` annotations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and conditional [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks using a `ParseContext` lookup to disable external link fetching by default. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the module fails to compile with a cascade of “illegal [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of type” and “identifier expected” errors around the inserted configuration [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass, culminating in an unmatched‐brace “reached end of file while parsing” error.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• A Jazzer fuzzing run on the Tika M3U8 parser produced a [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` exception.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The stack trace shows Tika’s `M3U8Parser.handleLink` invoking [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`URLConnection.connect`, leading to Jazzer’s SSRF sanitizer.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The exception indicates that untrusted input may drive arbitrary [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m requests[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand thus potentially expose internal services or exfiltrate data.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The patch removes an unused import [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`java.text.DecimalFormat`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and adds three new[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimports for Tika configuration [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.config.Field`, [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.config.Param`, `org.apache.tika.metadata.PropertyType`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• It declares a public nested class `M3U8ParserConfig` inside `M3U8Parser`, with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean field `allowExternalLinks`, defaulting to `false`, and annotated for Tika’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ParseContext` injection.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• In `handleLink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m161[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it injects code to:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Return early if the line does not start with “http”  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Lookup `M3U8ParserConfig` from the `ParseContext` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfallback to defaults if [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – If `allowExternalLinks` is false, return before any network operation  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• During compilation of `tika-parser-audiovideo-module`, the Java compiler reports [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabout [0m[1;36m35[0m[39m errors in `M3U8Parser.java`, all describing “illegal start of type” or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“<identifier> expected” at the lines where `M3U8ParserConfig` is declared.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• A final error “reached end of file while parsing” indicates mismatched or missing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbraces.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The flood of syntax errors suggests that the nested class and its imports were [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplaced in an incorrect location or that class‐level braces are unbalanced.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the cascade of syntax errors and restore correct SSRF‐guarding logic, we[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneed to reapply the original patch’s intent—introducing a nested configuration [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass and early‐return guard in handleLink—while fixing misplaced declarations and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbalanced braces.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Restore class‐level structure  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Remove the duplicate “public class M3U8Parser implements Parser [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m” that was [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minserted into the import section. The file should have exactly one top‐level class [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat line ~[0m[1;36m52[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Move all added imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.config.Field`, [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.config.Param`, `org.apache.tika.metadata.PropertyType`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so they [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msit immediately after the existing import block, before the single `public class [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mM3U8Parser` declaration.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Insert the nested config class at the correct scope  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Within the body of `public class M3U8Parser implements Parser [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbetween [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe static field declarations around line [0m[1;36m63[0m[39m and the first method definition[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe public static `M3U8ParserConfig` class. For example, right after the last [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`EXTVERSION`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or before the constructor/parse methods.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Ensure it is fully enclosed by the outer class’s braces [0m[1;39m([0m[39mopening at line [0m[1;36m52[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing at line [0m[1;36m200[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Verify no extra braces were added or removed.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Mirror Tika’s ParseContext pattern  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Declare a `private static final M3U8ParserConfig DEFAULT_CONFIG = new [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mM3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` inside the outer class.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In `handleLink`, replace the ad‐hoc `new [0m[1;35mM3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        PDFParser‐style lookup:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        M3U8ParserConfig cfg = DEFAULT_CONFIG;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        M3U8ParserConfig userCfg = [0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39muserCfg != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            cfg = userCfg;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcfg.isAllowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Keep the existing `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnextLine.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;` guard [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately before the config lookup.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify imports and brace balance  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Confirm imports are grouped correctly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjava.*, then org.apache.tika.*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Run a simple compile to check that the file has exactly one outer class, zero [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplicated braces, and the nested config class compiles.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • No changes to harness/test code.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Removing the duplicate class header resolves the “illegal start of type” errors [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered by a top‐level class declared inside imports.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Placing `M3U8ParserConfig` inside the existing class preserves the intended [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencapsulation and matches other parsers’ patterns.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Using a static default config + context‐lookup follows Tika’s established [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconvention [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., PDFParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring external link fetching remains disabled by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault without breaking any existing parsing logic.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– This strategy addresses the original SSRF vulnerability, eliminates syntax [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors, and maintains full compatibility with existing tests and fuzz‐harness.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.M3U8ParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:39[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b782adc79e9c6729[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run against the `M3U8Parser` in Apache Tika surfaced a Server-Side[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability: the parser unconditionally opens HTTP [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnections to URIs found in an M3U8 playlist. To mitigate this, a patch was [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproposed that adds a configurable flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowExternalLinks`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—disabled by [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault—to gate external link fetching. After introducing a nested [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`M3U8ParserConfig` class with Tika-style `@Field` and `@Param` annotations and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodifying the link-handling logic to check the flag, the module fails to compile. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe build breaks with “cannot find symbol” errors for `PropertyType`, missing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mannotation attributes on `@Field`, and an incompatible use of `@Param`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During fuzzing, Jazzer reported a `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when `M3U8Parser` tried to open a socket to `jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows `[0m[1;35mM3U8Parser.handleLink[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calling [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mURLConnection.getInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which triggers the SSRF sanitizer.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerability arises because `M3U8Parser` treats any URI prefix “http” as [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfair game for fetching, potentially exposing internal services or sensitive data.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `M3U8Parser.java`, a nested static class `M3U8ParserConfig` was added. It [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclares a boolean field `allowExternalLinks` with Tika configuration annotations:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `@[0m[1;35mField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkind = PropertyType.BOOLEAN, name = [0m[32m"parser.m3u8.allowExternalLinks"[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdescription = [0m[32m"..."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `@[0m[1;35mParam[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaultValue = [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A `DEFAULT_CONFIG` instance is created with `allowExternalLinks = false`. In [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`handleLink`, before fetching, code retrieves a user-supplied config from the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing context [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and only proceeds when [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcfg.isAllowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is true.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Imports were added:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.tika.config.Field`[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.tika.config.Param`[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.tika.metadata.PropertyType`[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maven compilation fails in the audio/video parser module with five errors:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `cannot find symbol: class PropertyType` in `org.apache.tika.metadata`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `@Field` has no `[0m[1;35mkind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` attribute[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Cannot resolve `PropertyType` in the `@Field` annotation[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `@Field` has no `[0m[1;35mdescription[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` attribute[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `org.apache.tika.config.Param` is not an annotation type [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincompatible [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconversion to `java.lang.annotation.Annotation`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey log excerpts:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - [0m[35m/[0m[95mM3U8Parser.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m32[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot find symbol class PropertyType  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - [0m[35m/[0m[95mM3U8Parser.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m71[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot find symbol method [0m[1;35mkind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on `@Field`  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - [0m[35m/[0m[95mM3U8Parser.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m71[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m23[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot find symbol variable PropertyType  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - [0m[35m/[0m[95mM3U8Parser.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m73[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot find symbol method [0m[1;35mdescription[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on `@Field`  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - [0m[35m/[0m[95mM3U8Parser.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m74[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m][0m[39m incompatible types: `Param` cannot be converted to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.lang.annotation.Annotation`[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The signature and package location of Tika’s `@Field` annotation: confirm [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupported attributes and correct import.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Presence and correct package of any `PropertyType` enum or equivalent in the Tika[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata module.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Whether there is a Tika annotation or mechanism for default parameter values, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe proper annotation to specify defaults.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How other parsers in the Tika codebase define and consume per-parser [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration via the `ParseContext`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The binding process that injects configuration objects into `ParseContext`—how to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregister `M3U8ParserConfig` so it can be retrieved at parse time.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the nested `M3U8ParserConfig` class, remove the `@[0m[1;35mParam[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaultValue = [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` annotation entirely.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the incorrect `@[0m[1;35mField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkind = PropertyType.BOOLEAN, …, description = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“…"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with the correct Tika `@Field` usage:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @[0m[1;35mField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname = [0m[32m"parser.m3u8.allowExternalLinks"[0m[39m, required = false[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private boolean allowExternalLinks = false;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – The default value is provided by the field initializer, matching Tika’s [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern in other parsers.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preserve the DEFAULT_CONFIG and runtime gating logic in `handleLink`:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static final M3U8ParserConfig DEFAULT_CONFIG = new [0m[1;35mM3U8ParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     so that the parser defaults to not fetching external links.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `handleLink`, continue to retrieve any user-supplied config from the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ParseContext`:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     M3U8ParserConfig cfg = DEFAULT_CONFIG;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     M3U8ParserConfig userCfg = [0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mM3U8ParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39muserCfg != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         cfg = userCfg;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcfg.isAllowExternalLinks[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This mirrors the pattern used in PDFParser and others, ensuring external [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetches are gated by configuration.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure only the `@Field` annotation from `org.apache.tika.config.Field` remains [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the config field:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Import:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import org.apache.tika.config.Field;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other config-related annotations are applied.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validate against existing tests and parsing harness:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since the fuzz harness and existing parser tests do not rely on the removed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mannotation attributes or the nonexistent `PropertyType`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`Param` classes, they will [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot be affected.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic for extracting and processing playlist links remains unchanged [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcept for the SSRF guard, which is disabled by default.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or external library code is modified, preserving the existing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing entrypoint.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Tika’s `@Field` annotation only supports `[0m[1;35mname[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mrequired[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. By stripping [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout `kind` and `description`, and dropping the incorrect `@Param`, the code [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiles cleanly.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The default flag value is still `false`, avoiding regressions in playlist parsing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior while preventing unwanted external fetches.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The pattern of context-based configuration follows established Tika parsers [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., PDFParserConfig[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so users familiar with Tika can enable this flag via [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstandard ParseContext configuration.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This single cohesive patch resolves all five “cannot find symbol” and type [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincompatibility errors without modifying harness, test, or utility code.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
